      "writtenOn": "2020-09-15T20:55:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t understand this comment; Historical seems to reference a single invocation (?), along with a timestamp (of what?).\n\nWhy is the (ID, Timestamp) pair important? Is Timestamp a property of ID, and so this is just caching it, or is the Timestamp independent of ID and calculated elsewhere? Whichever of these is the case, it would be good to document here (i.e. \"Timestamp is the cached creation time of ID\" or \"Timestamp is generated by $process and represents $thing\").\n\nHopefully there\u0027s a better name than Timestamp for the field?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 42,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 42,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "2d5893779757d02f1f7dd99fe0ffea0f0d716dc9",
