      "writtenOn": "2020-09-16T01:44:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point. Changing to IndexTimestamp\n\nIt represents the timestamp that a given invocation is indexed at, which may differ from its own creation timestamp, by virtue of being included by another invocation (whose timestamp _is_ in the index)\n\nThe new comment says \"// Historical is a reference to an invocation paired with the ordinal fields\n// that they are indexed under.\"",
