      "message": "Done, thanks. Old habits are hard to change. \n100 !\u003d 50 because 50 refers to indexed invocations, 100 refers to number of individual results.\nthe 50 is arbitrary, we should query as many indexed invocations as needed to fill the requested number of results (whether that\u0027s 1 or a 1000 will depend on the request)\nAnd 100 is just a sane default page size.\n\nI was wondering if we should accept a timeout in the request. E.g. \"Get me as many results matching this request as possible in up to 5 seconds (or the first 200 results, whatever\u0027s fastest)\"",
